<title> Researchers in information retrieval and HCI have extensively studied user interaction with web search systems, particularly for complex informational [16] or exploratory [55] search tasks. Such tasks typically comprise three stages [3, 43]: query formulation (i.e., generating and refining search keywords), search results triage (i.e., determining which parts of the search engine results page - the SERP - are most relevant to the task at hand, and which link to open), and information extraction (i.e., gathering and making sense of the sought-after content).

